# Security (sensitive health data)

This app stores personal medical information. Treat every change as security-relevant.

- **Auth everywhere**: server functions that touch user data call `requireUser()`. UI guards
  (`_authenticated` layout) are convenience only, never the sole gate.
- **Validate all input** with zod in the server function `.validator(...)` before use.
- **RLS is mandatory** for any new table; owner-scope it and add matching Storage policies.
- **Documents** are private: never expose public URLs; use signed URLs with type/size limits
  (`ALLOWED_MIME_TYPES`, `MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES` in `documents.schema.ts`).
- **Secrets**: only `VITE_*` values may reach the client. Never import the service-role key into
  client-reachable modules. Never commit real secrets (`.env` is gitignored; `.env.example` only).
- **HTTP headers/CSP** are centralized in `src/lib/server/security-headers.ts` (wired via
  `src/start.ts`). Update the CSP `connect-src` when adding new external origins.
- **Auth endpoints are rate-limited** (`src/lib/server/rate-limit.ts`); keep it on sign-in/up/reset.
- Auth responses stay generic to avoid user enumeration.
- CI runs `pnpm audit` + gitleaks; keep them green.
